-- Macy's to close nine stores, affects 899 jobs
-- 
-- Fri Dec 28, 2007 1:15pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/12/28/us-macys-closings-idUSWNAS538720071228

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Retailer Macy's Inc said on Friday it would close nine underperforming stores in Indiana, Ohio, Louisiana, Oklahoma, Utah and Texas. 

 Macy's said the closings would affect 899 employees, who would be offered positions in nearby stores where possible. It said employees laid off in the process would be provided severance benefits and outplacement assistance. (Reporting by  Bill Rigby , editing by Leslie Gevirtz)